The paper deals with the problem of aesthetic quality assessment of images containing human faces, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Convolutional Neural Networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves the prediction of aesthetics, which is a task related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also deals with human perception of images, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
